1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
A nontechnical user starts with one simple sentence.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:22,000
The IDE agent reads the repository rules, checks UiPath readiness, and registers a live governance gate.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:38,000
No project work starts until a real UiPath Action Center approval exists.

4
00:00:38,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Action Center hosts the explicit human approval task with a required approval checkbox.

5
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:16,000
The decision is submitted in UiPath. The agent does not trust a chat message as approval.

6
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:31,000
UiPath Data Fabric stores governance memory: CodeSoul, MinefieldHistory, Persona, and StateMemory.

7
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:46,000
The BPMN/agentic process canvas documents the orchestration design for the governed flow.

8
00:01:46,000 --> 00:02:25,000
After API verification succeeds, Phase 0 begins with one plain-language question at a time.

9
00:02:25,000 --> 00:03:01,000
The beginner answers practical business questions; the agent records each answer before continuing.

10
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:21,000
Phase 0 completes and creates a formal master plan before any raw code is written.

11
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:45,000
The repository contains the agent rules, UiPath connector, tests, and evidence for the governance flow.

12
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Universal Agent OS: beginner idea, governed approval, auditable plan.
